                'preview' => '	[{"id":"preset-root","type":"section","tagName":"div","attributes":{"attrs":{},"style":{"min-height":"150px","width":"600px","padding":"10px 10px 10px 10px","margin":"0 auto"}},"overrideAttributes":{"width":"600px"},"children":[{"type":"Gap","tagName":"div","meta":{"displayName":"Gap","imgSrc":"/images/builder/gap.svg","imgAlt":"gap-widget"},"attributes":{"attrs":{},"style":{"height":"20px"},"containerStyle":{"padding":"0px 0px 0px 0px"}},"overrideAttributes":{},"content":"","id":"tXpgGYAuq"},{"type":"Paragraph","tagName":"preview-text-editor","meta":{"displayName":"Paragraph","imgSrc":"/images/builder/paragraph.svg","imgAlt":"paragraph-widget"},"attributes":{"props":{"toolbar":false},"style":{"color":"#000000","font-size":"16px","font-weight":400,"font-style":"normal","text-decoration":"none","align":"left","text-align":"left","outline":"none","font-family":"Helvetica","line-height":"1.6","heading-size":"0px"},"containerStyle":{"padding":"10px 10px 10px 10px"}},"overrideAttributes":{},"content":"<div>In the 1920s, a psychologist, Zeigarnik was dining in a restaurant.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>She noticed the waiters were able to keep track of complex orders and unpaid meals.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>However, once the orders were fulfilled and paid, the waiters could not recall the detailed information about the orders.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>This is how <strong>The Zeigarnik Effect </strong>was discovered!</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>She found that people remember incomplete tasks more easily than tasks that have been completed!</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>But...</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>How can you use the Zeigarnik effect for your business?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>The answer is <strong>Cashback!</strong></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>What is Cashback?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Cashback is a rewards program that refunds your customers based on the amount spent in your online store.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>The refunds will be a form of credits, so when the customers buy from you again, they can use the credits to pay you.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><em>For example, a customer buys a 150 USD product from you, and the cashback reward is set to 10%.&nbsp;</em></div>\n<div><em>&nbsp;</em></div>\n<div><em>Which means, 15 USD will be stored as credits for the next purchase.</em></div>\n<div><em>&nbsp;</em></div>\n<div><em>So, the next time the customer buys a product for $150 from you again, the customer will only have to pay 135 USD.&nbsp;</em></div>\n<div><em>&nbsp;</em></div>\n<div><em>And now 13.5 USD will be stored as credits for the next purchase.</em></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>In other words, there will always be some unused credits in their accounts which keep them remembering to use it!</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>To make this more powerful, you can actually set an expiry date for the credits!</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>So they will come back more often!</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Can&rsquo;t wait to apply this small but powerful trick?&nbsp;</div>","id":"DgVe47S8J"},{"type":"Button","tagName":"a","meta":{"displayName":"Button","imgSrc":"/images/builder/button.svg","imgAlt":"button-widget"},"attributes":{"attrs":{"href":"https://help.hypershapes.com/help/cashback","target":"_blank"},"style":{"width":"max-content","max-width":"600px","display":"block","color":"#3366BB","background-color":"#FFFFFF","border":"none","border-radius":"2px","cursor":"pointer","padding":"10px 10px 10px 0px","font-size":"16px","font-family":"Helvetica","font-weight":400,"font-style":"normal","text-decoration":"underline","line-height":"1.6","align":"left","margin":"0 auto 0 0","pointer-events":"none"},"containerStyle":{"padding":"10px 10px 10px 10px"}},"overrideAttributes":{},"content":" Click here and set up for your business now.","id":"sAP4B6Xqx"},{"type":"Paragraph","tagName":"preview-text-editor","meta":{"displayName":"